This paper discusses the challenge of coherence in dialogue models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model that incorporates intentional structure, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates its proposed model on three different datasets, which involves experimentation and evaluation, making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the entity grid model, which is a technique for modelling patterns of distribution of entities across multiple sentences, making cs.SD (Sound) a possible sub-category as well.
